1
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:29,626
TALK TO HER

2
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,459
The stage is full of wooden
chairs and tables.

3
00:03:27,542 --> 00:03:31,043
Two women come out with robes.

4
00:03:31,501 --> 00:03:35,169
Their eyes are closed.
Like two sleepwalkers.

5
00:03:35,669 --> 00:03:39,919
You get scared... They trip
on everything, poor them.

6
00:03:40,253 --> 00:03:43,920
But suddenly, a man appears.

7
00:03:44,378 --> 00:03:49,046
With a very sad face, the
saddest I have ever seen.

8
00:03:49,546 --> 00:03:53,338
He pushes tables and chairs
out of their way.

9
00:03:55,297 --> 00:03:58,464
You can't imagine how touching
it was.

10
00:03:59,964 --> 00:04:03,715
Someone was sitting next to me.
In his 40s, hundsome.

11
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:08,299
He cried with emotion,
lots of times.

12
00:04:08,590 --> 00:04:12,633
I don't understand why...
It was very beautiful!

13
00:04:14,258 --> 00:04:16,467
I have a surprise for you!

14
00:04:24,676 --> 00:04:28,093
I have an autograph of
Rina Baus for you.

15
00:04:28,385 --> 00:04:30,969
I had to buy the photo.

16
00:04:33,428 --> 00:04:35,851
It is in english and says:

17
00:04:35,886 --> 00:04:39,387
I hope you surpass all
the obstacles...

18
00:04:39,845 --> 00:04:42,304
...and start dancing.

19
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:10,892
- She has her period.
- It's early.

20
00:06:22,111 --> 00:06:23,903
Good evening.

21
00:06:30,071 --> 00:06:32,821
Benigno, can you
stay tonight?

22
00:06:33,196 --> 00:06:36,572
My sister can't,
and I don't have anyone else.

23
00:06:36,863 --> 00:06:39,781
Why did you come?
You should have called.

24
00:06:39,906 --> 00:06:43,531
I am not taking advantage of you.
This week you did 3 nights.

25
00:06:43,906 --> 00:06:47,823
Don't worry. A free afternoon
is enough for me.

26
00:06:48,157 --> 00:06:51,782
I have to see the house
workers. It's a mess.

27
00:06:53,699 --> 00:06:56,290
And to frame a photo.

28
00:06:56,325 --> 00:07:00,784
My condition is not improving.
The hospital will decide.

29
00:07:01,326 --> 00:07:04,409
Your husband left you
and the children.

30
00:07:04,701 --> 00:07:08,452
Just come the nights you can.
We will be ok.

31
00:07:11,285 --> 00:07:13,327
Thanks a lot.

32
00:07:14,578 --> 00:07:18,078
- You cut off the intestinal food.
- She couldn't take it.

33
00:07:18,328 --> 00:07:21,620
- We will try again tomorrow.
- Yes, go now.

34
00:07:22,954 --> 00:07:24,954
And keep the spirits up!

35
00:07:32,289 --> 00:07:37,164
Six bulls and a woman.
Wednesday at Briuega.

36
00:07:38,373 --> 00:07:42,165
Lydia P Gonzales will
fight six bulls.

37
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:46,833
Why such a drastic decision?

38
00:07:46,958 --> 00:07:50,625
It's my job. 2 bulls, or 6.
Whatever they say.

39
00:07:51,042 --> 00:07:54,417
People say a lot of bullfighters
won't fight with you...

40
00:07:54,452 --> 00:07:56,810
...because you are a woman.

41
00:07:56,845 --> 00:07:59,168
People can say what they want.

42
00:07:59,501 --> 00:08:03,043
Too much chauvinism in bullfighting,
but there are exceptions.

43
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:08,419
Nino Valencia was happy to share
billing with you for several months.

44
00:08:11,503 --> 00:08:14,587
Do you think he did it
to promote himself?

45
00:08:14,962 --> 00:08:17,296
And when he succeeded that,
he abandoned you?

46
00:08:17,587 --> 00:08:20,629
I told you, I don't want
to talk about this!

47
00:08:20,963 --> 00:08:23,963
But by talking about
certain problems...

48
00:08:23,998 --> 00:08:26,964
...is the first step
towards their solution.

49
00:08:26,999 --> 00:08:29,673
- Nino Valencia...
- Enough!

50
00:08:30,048 --> 00:08:33,798
My dear Lydia, let me
finish the question.

51
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:37,549
I am not discussing this.
I told you earlier.

52
00:08:37,674 --> 00:08:42,091
You didn't say anything earlier!
It's bad what you are saying!

53
00:08:42,126 --> 00:08:45,265
They will think
it's a fixed interview.

54
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:49,259
And I am on of the few who
dare say the truth...

55
00:08:49,467 --> 00:08:52,516
...and you should dare accept

56
00:08:52,551 --> 00:08:55,885
...that Nino Valencia
took advantage of you.

57
00:08:56,302 --> 00:09:00,969
He shared with you not only
the fame, but sex as well.

58
00:09:01,004 --> 00:09:04,553
And he left you when
time was right.

59
00:09:05,970 --> 00:09:09,137
Juan Luis, Marco here...
How are you?

60
00:09:09,762 --> 00:09:12,012
I want to ask you something.

61
00:09:12,721 --> 00:09:16,305
I would like to do an article
about Lydia Gonzales.

62
00:09:17,263 --> 00:09:19,555
Yes, I see it too...

63
00:09:22,306 --> 00:09:25,181
I would like to do something
deep.

64
00:09:27,181 --> 00:09:30,474
For the Sunday issue?
Great...

65
00:10:26,691 --> 00:10:30,733
- The woman has gone crazy!
- She dedicates it to you.

66
00:10:31,150 --> 00:10:34,984
She would let the bull injur
her, just so that you see it.

67
00:10:35,525 --> 00:10:38,651
You shouldn't have come,
especially you.

68
00:11:29,617 --> 00:11:32,743
Don't tell me anything.
I know what I am doing.

69
00:11:33,201 --> 00:11:37,285
Nino should concentrate.
He doesn't want any more worries.

70
00:11:37,660 --> 00:11:41,702
Nothing to worry about. He should
just come to pick up his stuff.

71
00:11:42,452 --> 00:11:46,328
- Or tell me where to send them.
- Send them at my place.

72
00:11:46,363 --> 00:11:50,204
He, himself, should say so.
This is nothing to do with you.

73
00:11:52,746 --> 00:11:55,246
You can leave whenever you want.

74
00:11:55,579 --> 00:11:58,455
- Good evening.
- Scotch on the rocks, please.

75
00:11:58,490 --> 00:12:01,830
- What glass do you prefer?
- A tall one.

76
00:12:06,623 --> 00:12:09,748
Can I talk to you for
a minute, please?

77
00:12:11,499 --> 00:12:14,791
Forget it. When something is
over, it's over.

78
00:12:16,374 --> 00:12:20,167
- What are you saying?
- Can I talk to you?

79
00:12:23,084 --> 00:12:26,709
If you take me to Madrid,
we can talk on the way.

80
00:12:26,744 --> 00:12:28,918
It will be my pleasure.

81
00:12:42,128 --> 00:12:45,504
- Who named you Lydia;
- My father.

82
00:12:45,754 --> 00:12:49,004
It's as if he sealed your destiny.

83
00:12:49,129 --> 00:12:53,588
He always wanted to be a bullfighter,
but stayed a banderillero.

84
00:12:54,339 --> 00:12:58,172
He is the one that was there
for me, more than anyone else.

85
00:12:58,631 --> 00:13:01,006
But he died last year.

86
00:13:02,340 --> 00:13:04,382
I am sorry.

87
00:13:05,049 --> 00:13:08,549
'El Pais' wants me to do a profile
on you for their Sunday issue.

88
00:13:08,841 --> 00:13:12,341
Do you write on bullfighting?
I don't know your name.

89
00:13:12,550 --> 00:13:15,884
To be honest,
I know nothing of it.

90
00:13:17,134 --> 00:13:20,968
But I know a lot about
desperate women.

91
00:13:21,384 --> 00:13:24,802
And who told you I am
desperate?

92
00:13:25,135 --> 00:13:28,719
- This is the impression I have.
- Bullfighting doesn't interest you.

93
00:13:28,754 --> 00:13:31,886
You are interested in my
relationship with Nino Valencia.

94
00:13:32,178 --> 00:13:35,345
Tell El Pais to leave me alone!

95
00:14:14,726 --> 00:14:17,393
- Take me from here!
- What's going on?

96
00:14:17,476 --> 00:14:21,269
Take me from here! There is
a snake in the kitchen.

97
00:14:21,602 --> 00:14:24,769
- Give me the keys.
- The door is open.

98
00:14:25,061 --> 00:14:27,353
Calm down.
And stay there.

99
00:16:01,284 --> 00:16:03,368
My purse.

100
00:16:05,285 --> 00:16:07,827
Take me to a hotel.

101
00:16:08,202 --> 00:16:10,994
I am never coming back to
this house.

102
00:16:11,744 --> 00:16:15,536
- To which hotel?
- To Eurobuilding, lets say.

103
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:48,667
Don't tell anyone about
the snake, please.

104
00:16:49,583 --> 00:16:52,334
Only my family knows.

105
00:16:52,459 --> 00:16:55,834
I always respect other
people's phobias.

106
00:16:56,209 --> 00:17:00,502
After what you have done, how
can I say no to to the profile?

107
00:17:01,294 --> 00:17:05,419
Think about it again. I will
call tomorrow, tell me then.

108
00:17:06,253 --> 00:17:08,628
Thanks for everything.

109
00:17:31,798 --> 00:17:35,757
Do you want me to stay? I can
sleep in the sofa.

110
00:17:35,966 --> 00:17:39,258
No, I need to get used to
being alone.

111
00:18:21,889 --> 00:18:23,848
Do you wash her?

112
00:18:24,140 --> 00:18:26,098
What do you think?

113
00:18:26,807 --> 00:18:29,557
- How was the night?
- normal.

114
00:18:29,974 --> 00:18:33,683
- Give it to me. I will do it.
- I am going now.

115
00:18:33,891 --> 00:18:36,267
- Good bye.
- Bye, Matilde.

116
00:18:39,767 --> 00:18:41,851
It's so hot!

117
00:18:42,309 --> 00:18:46,018
- Lets cut her hair.
- short, it's more practical.

118
00:18:46,977 --> 00:18:50,144
We will leave it as it was
when she came here...

119
00:18:50,435 --> 00:18:53,436
...so that she is not surprised
when she wakes up.

120
00:18:53,471 --> 00:18:56,561
After 4 years, it will be great.

121
00:18:56,645 --> 00:18:59,228
I believe in miracles.
So should you.

122
00:18:59,263 --> 00:19:02,354
- Why me?
- Because you need them.

123
00:19:02,604 --> 00:19:06,813
One might happen to you,
and you will not know.

124
00:19:07,563 --> 00:19:09,688
So hot!

125
00:19:09,938 --> 00:19:12,070
I took something from the
drugstore...

126
00:19:12,105 --> 00:19:15,231
...to help stop the perspiration
stains on my uniform.

127
00:19:15,648 --> 00:19:19,232
My armpits are ok,
but look at my face.

128
00:19:19,267 --> 00:19:21,690
- What's it called?
- Perspirex.

129
00:19:30,442 --> 00:19:33,025
It's Marco...
Remember me?

130
00:19:33,817 --> 00:19:36,359
- How are you?
- Naked.

131
00:19:41,818 --> 00:19:44,819
I need to buy some clothes.
That's all I've got.

132
00:19:45,319 --> 00:19:47,903
I can bring you some
from your place.

133
00:19:48,278 --> 00:19:51,487
I don't want anything from there.
Maybe another time.

134
00:19:51,820 --> 00:19:54,029
- Where are we going?
- To Sybilla.

135
00:19:54,279 --> 00:19:56,821
- You think I am crazy.
- Why?

136
00:19:57,112 --> 00:20:00,738
- Because I don't want to go home.
- No, I understand.

137
00:20:01,196 --> 00:20:05,489
When I separated, I couldn't
sleep in the same bed...

138
00:20:05,864 --> 00:20:09,031
I was sleeping in the sofa,
in the living room.

139
00:20:09,239 --> 00:20:13,615
For a week. Until I finally
bought a new bed.

140
00:20:14,032 --> 00:20:16,240
So, you are separated.

141
00:20:17,032 --> 00:20:18,991
I am alone.

142
00:20:19,949 --> 00:20:23,700
AFTER A FEW MONTHS

143
00:20:41,619 --> 00:20:44,411
Marco, we should
talk afterwards.

144
00:20:44,745 --> 00:20:48,329
- We've been talking for an hour.
- You have, not me.

145
00:20:49,412 --> 00:20:51,371
Indeed.

146
00:21:20,125 --> 00:21:24,668
Did you read about the nuns
that got raped by the misionaries?

147
00:21:26,376 --> 00:21:30,252
Priests, themselves!
It's horrible!

148
00:21:30,794 --> 00:21:33,794
Yeah, they've gone bad too!
Where are we heading to?

149
00:21:33,829 --> 00:21:36,378
First they raped the locals.

150
00:21:36,836 --> 00:21:40,253
Then, due to AIDS, they started
raping nuns.

151
00:21:41,212 --> 00:21:43,962
And I admired them so much!

152
00:21:44,337 --> 00:21:47,088
Not all of them are rapists,
for sure.

153
00:21:47,421 --> 00:21:50,255
No, some of them are
pedophiles.

154
00:21:50,630 --> 00:21:54,422
- What's that? Everyone loves fucking.
- Antonio, you are an animal!

155
00:21:56,298 --> 00:21:59,381
- How do the bulls look?
- Good, but fat.

156
00:21:59,881 --> 00:22:03,090
- How much do you think?
- Over 500 kilos.

157
00:22:03,924 --> 00:22:07,758
I am going to the bar. And don't
forget, we are eating home.

158
00:22:08,091 --> 00:22:11,508
If the kids don't see their aunt,
there'll be hell to pay.

159
00:25:31,956 --> 00:25:34,748
Don't cry, my love.

160
00:25:44,666 --> 00:25:47,667
- How is it?
- Very bad.

161
00:25:47,702 --> 00:25:49,542
It tore her apart.

162
00:25:49,625 --> 00:25:52,216
The father will be happy now!

163
00:25:52,251 --> 00:25:56,627
'Not the little one!', we kept
telling him, my mother and I.

164
00:25:59,169 --> 00:26:02,086
And yet, she became like him.

165
00:26:02,121 --> 00:26:04,419
Don't be upset.

166
00:26:05,378 --> 00:26:07,587
What time is it?

167
00:26:07,837 --> 00:26:10,004
It has been four hours.

168
00:26:11,379 --> 00:26:14,338
AFTER THREE WEEKS

169
00:26:15,713 --> 00:26:17,886
Are you going to Cordoba?

170
00:26:17,921 --> 00:26:21,714
Yes... I would like to stay,
but I can't.

171
00:26:21,797 --> 00:26:25,381
We can't do anything extra.

172
00:26:25,506 --> 00:26:27,971
The bar's been closed for 20 days.

173
00:26:28,006 --> 00:26:31,590
The kids are with the neigbhour,
and I've neglected the other one.

174
00:26:31,882 --> 00:26:35,424
If something happens, can
you be here in 2 hours?

175
00:26:35,883 --> 00:26:40,050
- Rest assured for that.
- We have to have faith.

176
00:26:42,175 --> 00:26:44,891
I light some candles...

177
00:26:44,926 --> 00:26:47,968
...but I find it very
difficult to have faith.

178
00:26:48,676 --> 00:26:51,927
When can we put her medals
back on her?

179
00:26:52,969 --> 00:26:54,892
Not yet.

180
00:26:54,927 --> 00:26:59,220
With all these...
wounds, the tracheotomy...

181
00:27:02,262 --> 00:27:04,554
She never took them off.

182
00:27:18,764 --> 00:27:20,890
I will get a vase.

183
00:27:40,684 --> 00:27:43,935
I have to go to the US
for three months.

184
00:27:44,435 --> 00:27:47,644
It is very important,
says my agent.

185
00:27:47,977 --> 00:27:52,019
And yet... the way things
stand here...

186
00:27:54,937 --> 00:27:57,479
...I don't want to go.

187
00:28:10,647 --> 00:28:13,814
Can you get out for
a moment, please?

188
00:28:23,358 --> 00:28:26,441
No smoking here.

189
00:28:29,067 --> 00:28:31,359
Did she talk to you that day?

190
00:28:33,192 --> 00:28:36,610
- Or rather, I talked.
- And what did you say?

191
00:28:38,027 --> 00:28:40,152
Things that concern me.

192
00:28:40,985 --> 00:28:43,951
Did she tell you anything
about me?

193
00:28:43,986 --> 00:28:48,111
Honestly, Lydia hadn't talked
about you for a long time.

194
00:28:48,987 --> 00:28:53,529
- It's my fault for what happened.
- No, it's my fault.

195
00:33:00,609 --> 00:33:03,776
Caetano made me
freak out.

196
00:33:07,152 --> 00:33:10,819
Marco, I've always wanted
to ask you something.

197
00:33:11,069 --> 00:33:14,903
Why did you cry that night,
after you killed the snake?

198
00:33:16,695 --> 00:33:19,195
It brought me lots of memories.

199
00:33:20,945 --> 00:33:24,571
Years ago, I had to
kill another snake.

200
00:33:24,946 --> 00:33:27,155
We were in Africa.

201
00:33:27,613 --> 00:33:30,704
She had the same phobia as you.

202
00:33:30,739 --> 00:33:35,989
She was waiting outside the tent,
terrified, defenseless...

203
00:33:37,365 --> 00:33:39,698
...and totally naked...

204
00:33:41,407 --> 00:33:44,824
...because she had seen the snake,
while we were asleep.

205
00:33:45,199 --> 00:33:48,491
Was it the same one who made
you sleep in the living room?

206
00:33:50,908 --> 00:33:53,367
I hate that woman.

207
00:33:53,825 --> 00:33:57,493
- I haven't seen her for years.
- Even worse.

208
00:33:57,528 --> 00:34:00,618
What can I do to make you
forget her?

209
00:34:00,827 --> 00:34:03,285
Exactly what you are doing now.

210
00:34:34,082 --> 00:34:37,999
You were sound asleep. We didn't
want to wake you up.

211
00:34:39,958 --> 00:34:43,708
- Is Dr Vega here?
- He is in his office.

212
00:35:25,756 --> 00:35:28,965
Rosa, close the door.
There's a draft.

213
00:35:29,757 --> 00:35:33,008
- She opened her eyes.
- That gives me the creeps!

214
00:35:33,299 --> 00:35:36,466
- And when she yawns?
- I shit myself!

215
00:35:38,383 --> 00:35:41,634
Good morning, doctor.
I want to talk to you.

216
00:35:42,217 --> 00:35:44,593
How are you? Did you sleep well?

217
00:35:45,551 --> 00:35:47,176
I will buy you coffee.

218
00:35:48,927 --> 00:35:52,261
How long for might Lydia
stay like that?

219
00:35:52,552 --> 00:35:56,386
Months... years...
maybe for the rest of her life...

220
00:35:57,386 --> 00:35:59,845
There is no hope?

221
00:36:01,304 --> 00:36:04,887
As a doctor, I have to say
no... However...

222
00:36:05,179 --> 00:36:07,221
RESUSCITATION

223
00:36:07,638 --> 00:36:11,138
Meryl Moon wakes up after
15 years in a coma.

224
00:36:11,472 --> 00:36:14,687
She went into a coma during
childbirth.

225
00:36:14,722 --> 00:36:19,181
Meryl was a PVS, persistent
vegetative state, like Lydia, for life.

226
00:36:20,056 --> 00:36:23,349
Her recovery contradicts
everything I am about to say.

227
00:36:23,384 --> 00:36:25,349
That is, that there is hope.

228
00:36:25,766 --> 00:36:28,231
I insist. Scientifically, no.

229
00:36:28,266 --> 00:36:31,517
But if you want to have faith,
OK.

230
00:36:31,850 --> 00:36:35,274
Is she opening her eyes?
Or I imagine this?

231
00:36:35,309 --> 00:36:39,893
She does, but that doesn't mean
she is aware of anything.

232
00:36:40,435 --> 00:36:44,477
Her brain cell has been
completely destroyed.

233
00:36:45,019 --> 00:36:49,811
However, it can control
the automatic functions...

234
00:36:50,228 --> 00:36:54,812
such as breathing, sleeping,
waking up and intestinal functions.

235
00:36:54,847 --> 00:36:57,694
She opens her eyes,
but mechanically.

236
00:36:57,729 --> 00:37:01,105
Her brain is dead. She has
no ideas and feelings.

237
00:37:16,023 --> 00:37:18,524
Come in, please.

238
00:37:30,276 --> 00:37:33,401
- My name is Benigno.
- Marco Zuloaga

239
00:37:33,568 --> 00:37:35,735
This is Alicia.

240
00:37:40,694 --> 00:37:43,159
Was it your first night here?

241
